CatDescriptText: The church was located on the corner of Boyle and Hemlock Streets. It had light colored brick, large stained glass windows, and a steeple with two colors of slate in a striped pattern.
TitMainTitle: Group of men and women outside Brown Chapel A. M. E. Church, Rev. C. S. Spivey, Jr., minister, Webster Avenue, Hill District
